51.3	Battle	Battle	Generally, a battle is a conceptual component in the hierarchy of combat in warfare between two or more armed forces, or combatants. In a battle, each combatant will seek to defeat the others, with defeat determined by the conditions of a military campaign. Battles generally are well defined in duration, area and force commitment.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Sadler%2C_Battle_of_Waterloo.jpg/400px-Sadler%2C_Battle_of_Waterloo.jpg
